definition: the five fingers of one's hand
finger/to point at or to/to indicate or refer to/to depend on/to count on/(of hair) to stand on end
Wuzhi Mountain (1,840 m), highest mountain in Hainan/Wuzhishan City, Hainan

pinyin: shen1 shou3 bu4 jian4 wu3 zhi3

sentences.english: Bounty hunters trying to stop her from reaching Five Elements Mountain.
sentences.chinese: 玉疆殺手想阻止我去五指山。

sentences.english: Neil: And she couldn't see her hand in front of her.
sentences.chinese: 她說煙霧大得她伸手都不見五指。

sentences.english: The "Guangdong green" jade deposit is situated in Wuzhishan area, Ningxian county, Guangdong Province.
sentences.chinese: “廣東綠”玉石礦牀發育於廣東省廣寧縣五指山地區。

sentences.english: The boy, unable to see in dark, walked slowly upstairs.
sentences.chinese: 那個男孩在伸手不見五指的黑暗中，慢慢地走上樓去。

sentences.english: We have local wild vegetables from Wuzhi Mountain.
sentences.chinese: 我們店裏有正宗的五指山野菜。

sentences.english: I couldn't see through the thick darkness.
sentences.chinese: 在伸手不見五指的黑暗中，我什麼也看不見。

sentences.english: Objective To obtain the reference normal physiological parameters of Wuzhishan pig(WZSP).
sentences.chinese: 目的建立中國實驗用五指山小型豬正常生理參考值。

sentences.english: Basically, one should use five fingers to hold a Chinese writing brush and keep the shaft upright.
sentences.chinese: 拿中國毛筆的方法一般是五指執筆法，筆桿要豎直。

sentences.english: The purpose of this experiment was to find out the best time for collection of miniature pig zygotes.
sentences.chinese: 本試驗擬探索出採集五指山小型豬原核胚的最佳時間。

sentences.english: To investigate the quality of different parts of Radix Fici Hirtae.
sentences.chinese: 確定五指毛桃不同採收部位的質量。

sentences.english: I awakened in the black and couldn't even see my hand.
sentences.chinese: 我在黑夜中醒來，四周漆黑，伸手不見五指。

sentences.english: The window is still black, dark, moonless.
sentences.chinese: 窗外依舊黑，不見五指，沒有月光。

sentences.english: It is said that the Five Element Mountains is from Hercules' hand.
sentences.chinese: 傳說那巍然屺立的五指山就是黎族祖先大力神的巨手。

sentences.english: The window is still black, wind and cold, dark, moonless.
sentences.chinese: 窗外依舊黑，風且涼，不見五指，沒有月光。

sentences.english: Mountain areas around the tropical forests, layer upon layer, not Weiyi.
sentences.chinese: 五指山區遍佈熱帶原始森林，層層疊疊，逶迤不盡。

sentences.english: In three days they went a hundred and eighty kilometres and reached the Five Fingers.
sentences.chinese: 三天時間裏，它們跑了一百八十公里，到了“五指”。

definition: to draw together/to place side by side (e.g. one's fingers, two halves of a torn sheet of paper etc)
to detain/to hold back by force/to buckle/to hook
delicate hands/woman's tender and soft hands
palm (of one's hand)/control (extended meaning from having something in the palm of one's hand)
